observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

Require the BAC Secretariat to submit the minutes or proceedings of pre-bid conference for Projects H and I;

Instruct the TWG and BAC to thoroughly verify and validate the SLCC duly supported with Certificate of Final Acceptance and/or Contractor’s Performance Evaluation Summary Final Rating including the other eligibility requirements submitted by the bidders in order to ensure that the government contracts are awarded to qualified bidders;

Require the BAC to:

Observe the prescribed periods in the posting of Performance Security, Notice of Award, Notice to Proceed and Supplemental Bid Bulletin;

Ensure that winning bidders comply with the posting of surety bonds callable upon demand as performance securities duly certified by the Insurance Commission before the awarding and signing of the contract;

Ensure that the Contract Agreement is in conformity with the GPPB prescribed templates and Philippine Bidding Documents, 6th Edition;

Ensure that the list of contractor’s major equipment units leased or under lease agreement pledged to the contracts is supported with certification of availability of equipment issued by the lessor/vendor for the duration of the project; and

Secure CSHP duly approved by the DOLE prior to the start of the project and submit the same as part of the contract agreement relative to procurement of infrastructure projects.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that progress and final payments relative to implementation of infrastructure projects are supported with the required documentation.

We recommended that Management direct:

The MDRRMO to:

Ensure that the PPAs included in LDRRMFIP are directly related to DRRM purposes;

Prepare LDRRMFIP in accordance with Annex A of COA Circular No. 2012-002, copy furnished the Audit Team, to support the release and use of current year and prior years’ unexpended balances of LDRRMF which should be the basis of the MPDC for inclusion in the AIP;

Provide specific titles based on the intended purpose and manner of implementation of the PPAs under the LDRRMF in the LDRRMFIP so as to ensure alignment of expenses to the respective approved PPAs; and

Submit monthly report on sources and utilization on DRRMF on or before the 15th day of the ensuing month.

The Municipal Budget Officer to:

Stop charging unrelated expenses or expenses not directly related to DRRM activities to ensure strict compliance with relevant provisions in the proper utilization of the LDRRMF;

Certify only purchase requests which are in line with the approved PPAs under the LDRRMF.

We recommended that Management instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Treasurer as well as all accountable officers concerned, to:
Strictly comply with the timely preparation and submission of DVs and all other documents relevant to the transactions;
Immediately submit the 1,179 DVs and their supporting documents totaling ₱169,890,721.28 to the Audit Team;
Ensure that no DV shall be paid unless properly documented and/or approved by proper officials; and
Ensure that all financial transaction documents from the Treasury Office are promptly turned over to the Accounting Office for timely recording of transactions, and thereby, contribute to the timely submission of accounts to the Audit Team.

We recommended that Management require the OIC – Municipal Accountant to:
Monitor and ensure timely liquidation of cash advances within the required period. Send demand letters and strictly enforce the withholding of salaries of officials and employees who fail to fully liquidate their cash advances within the required period, in coordination with the Municipal Treasurer;
Refrain from accepting partial liquidations and record the liquidation of cash advances only upon the submission of complete supporting documents and/or the refund of any excess or unutilized cash advance, supported by an official receipt. Likewise, require the accountable officer to properly accomplish the LR by indicating the OR number and the date of refund and/or issuance of OR;
Ensure that no additional cash advance will be granted to accountable officers with an outstanding cash advance;
Ensure proper recording of cash advances in accordance with the Revised Chart of Accounts;
Refrain from allowing cash advances for special purpose/time-bound undertakings to officials and employees who are not duly appointed/designated as SDOs and are not bonded;
Ensure that management limits the grant of cash advance to duly designated SDOs who are properly bonded and whose duties permit or require the possession or custody of government funds in accordance with applicable laws, rules, and regulations;
Immediately submit the aforementioned 13 liquidation reports and henceforth ensure the timely submission thereof to the Audit Team; and
Require the duly designated SDO/s to maintain a cashbook to monitor the liquidations of cash advances granted to them.

We recommended that Management direct the BAC to:
Ensure that a copy of APP is attached in DVs to support the payment of procured goods/services;
Ensure the preparation of a BAC resolution recommending and justifying to the HoPE the use of an alternative method of procurement, as well as obtaining the approval of the HoPE prior to resorting to an alternative method of procurement;
Ensure that the delegation has been properly authorized by the BAC through a resolution approved by the HoPE, if they opt to delegate to the end-user or appropriate committee the canvassing or serving of RFQ;
Update or revise the RFQ form to include the suppliers PhilGEPS Registration Number and require them to supply the said information along with their price quotation;
Make the necessary postings in the PhilGEPS for procurements above ₱50,000.00 to maintain transparency and encourage fair competition in the procurement process; and
Require from the supplier the submission of documents necessary in the use of alternative method of procurement - SVP.
We further recommended that Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
Submit the lacking documents and ensure that all the documentary requirements are complete before certification; and
See to it that all disbursements involving procurement of goods and services undertaken through alternative method of procurement are duly supported with complete documentary requirements.

We recommended that Management:
Cause the refund of granted cash awards and prizes totaling to ₱85,500.00, if warranted, based on the absence of specific legal basis;
Instruct the OIC - Municipal Accountant, with the assistance of the BAC Secretariat and other concerned employee/s, to immediately submit the lacking documents mentioned above for review and evaluation of the Audit Team;
Instruct the BAC to strictly observe the required procurement process under the “Negotiated Procurement - Lease of Real Property and Venue” mode of procurement; and
Instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Municipal Treasurer, to discontinue the practice of granting cash advances to employees for the payment of venue rentals. Instead, payments should be made directly to the lessors through issuance of checks.

We recommended that Management:
a. Instruct the Municipal Budget Officer to present additional allowances/ honoraria of national government officials in the LGU budget under the MOOE allotment;
b. Instruct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to record payment of allowances/honoraria to national government officials as Other Professional Services and prepare the necessary adjusting journal entry for the communication allowances recorded as Honoraria. The proposed adjusting journal entry is as follows;
Account Debit Credit
Telephone Expenses 5,000.00
Honoraria 5,000.00

We recommended that Management:
a. Instruct the Inspection Committee to conduct inspection of and verify deliveries as to quantity and conformity to specifications based on the DR and approved PO/contract and indicate notation, if any, on the AIR if deliveries are not in conformity to specifications or incomplete;
b. Instruct the GSO to: return the items to the supplier, in case, deliver ies did not conform to the specifications and require the latter to comply with the agreed specifications and/or terms of the contract; and require the suppliers of delivered IT equipment to replace or make necessary adjustments to meet the indicated specifications in the contract.

We recommended that Management:
Direct the Municipal Administrator and the OIC-Municipal Accountant to strictly adhere to existing laws, rules and regulations on the proper application of cash advance and ensure that payments shall be made by check directly payable to the creditor so that applicable withholding taxes can be deducted and remitted to the national government;
Require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to issue demand letters to municipal officials and employees to remind them of their responsibility to settle their unliquidated cash advances; 
Require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to strictly monitor the submission of liquidation reports to ensure timely accounting thereof to avoid undue accumulation of outstanding cash advances; and
Require the Municipal Treasurer to withhold the salaries of the municipal officials and employees with unliquidated cash advances pursuant to Section 37 of PD No. 1445 considering that they have been notified and given more adequate time to liquidate their cash advances.

