We recommended that Management:
Direct the Municipal GSO to prepare the Property Inventory Form and submit the same to the GSIS as the basis for the assessment of general insurance coverage of all insurable assets of the Municipality using the format prescribed in COA Circular No. 2018 - 002;
Instruct the Head of the Appraisal Committee to cause the appraisal of insurable properties of the LGU;
Require the Municipal Budget Officer to provide sufficient amount in the Annual Budget to pay for the premiums of all insurable assets; and
Instruct the GSO to secure the property insurance of non-insured government properties.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended Management the following courses of action:
Create an Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of public infrastructures especially the local road networks;
Require the Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of local roads under the jurisdiction and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Local Road Network at the end of the accounting period;
Direct the OIC - Municipal Accountant to maintain Local Road Network Ledger Card;
Inform the OIC - General Services Officer or Property Officer to periodically render Report on Local Road Networks, and furnish copies to the concerned offices. Also, the Municipal Engineer’s Office should provide the OIC - Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer or Property Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
Ensure coordination among LGU Offices to properly implement the accounting and reporting guidelines of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 5, 2015.
